-- Shell Opens Distillate Desulfurization Unit at Pernis Refinery
-- B y   J o h n   B u c k l e y
-- 2012-06-14T08:32:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-14/shell-opens-distillate-desulfurization-unit-at-pernis-refinery.html
Royal Dutch Shell Plc (RDSA)  commissioned a
$500 million distillate desulfurization at its Pernis refinery
in Rotterdam.  The new facility will enable the refiner to increase the
production of low-sulfur diesel and heating oil, according to an
e-mailed statement from the company based in The Hague.  Pernis,  Europe ’s biggest refinery, has a capacity of about
400,000 barrels a day, according to Shell’s  website .  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Buckley in Amsterdam at 
